Use gameWrapper-&gt;GetBakkesModPath() and use that as the base path to write to (this will be %appdata%/bakkesmod/bakkesmod). This works for both Epic and Steam installs
Make sure you&rsquo;ve included fstream
#include &lt;fstream&gt;C++17
std::ofstream stream( gameWrapper-&gt;GetBakkesModPath() / &#34;data&#34; / &#34;abc.txt&#34; ); std::ofstream stream( gameWrapper-&gt;GetDataFolder() / &#34;abc.txt&#34; ); //Note the removal of &#34;data&#34; stream &lt;&lt; &#34;def&#34;; // %appdata%/bakkesmod/bakkesmod/data/abc.txt now includes &#34;def&#34; Older C++
//Note that windows paths require wide strings, so need to use the L to indicate a wide string std::ofstream stream( gameWrapper-&gt;GetBakkesModPathW() + L&#34;data/abc.
